\b \cf2 What is it?
\b0 \cf0 \
Uli's Moose is a program that brings a moose on your screen from time to time that says something witty, funny or utterly useless.\
\

\b \cf2 How do I install it?
\b0 \cf0 \
Just copy the program named "Moose" into your "Applications" folder (If you don't have admin privileges, create an "Applications" folder in your home folder and put it in there). Then double-click the "Moose" application and click the "Launch at Startup" check box on the "Options" page so the Moose will show up the next time you log in. The Moose has an FAQ in its "Help" menu that should answer any other questions you may have.\
\

\b \cf2 How do I remove it?
\b0 \cf0 \
You really want to do that? Oh well, just delete the "Moose" application (or quit it and move it  out of the "Applications" folder) and the Moose will be gone. If you want to get rid of the Moose only temporarily, simply quit it.\
\

\b \cf2 What are the system requirements?
\b0 \cf0 \
Uli's Moose 3.5 should run on Mac OS X 10.3 or higher. If that doesn't work for you, or you are running Mac OS X 10.1, download the older version 3.0.5, which actually runs on anything up to 10.3.\
\

